    <h3>About Rapyd Framework</h3>

    <p>
        Rapyd is a PHP microframework for PHP 5.3 built on top of Slim Framework, Twig, Symfony Forms, Illuminate/Database, Bootstrap 3.
        It implement <strong>MVC</strong> and <strong>CRUDL</strong> patterns. <br />
        <br />
        There is no much documentation about Rapyd, so this demo mudule is the way to find how to make things.<br /> 
        Please do not hit me, Rapyd is built on top of well-documented projects.<br /> 
    </p>

    
    <h3>How it works</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Rapyd extend Slim application to give you an MVC with modular separation, you can define routes as in slim</li>
        <li>You can write your entities/models using Eloquent orm, define relationships bw entities in few line of code</li>
        <li>Render method in your controllers search for Twig view to display data</li>
        <li>Widgets: the boring part of our job is to build grids, paged results, forms, etc.. So Rapyd has ready to use classes to do that and a simple integration with symfony forms</li>
        <li>HTML: this demo module, and all widgets are made to work with Boostrap 3, so they are responsive, themeable.. and clean</li>
    </ul>

    
    <h3>Reference</h3>
    <p>
        <a href="http://www.slimframework.com/">Slim Framework</a><br />
        slim is basically a magnificent router, It's used as base of Rapyd/Application<br />
        (a layer to implement <strong>Controllers</strong> and manage modules organization, routing etc.)
    </p>
    

    <p>
        <a href="http://twig.sensiolabs.org/">Twig</a><br />
